results.name: Number of lambda-parking functions of the unique strict partition lambda with parts i_1<i_2<...<i_m and encoding n = Product_{j=1..m} prime(i_j-j+1).
comment: A strict partition is a partition into distinct parts.
link: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..20000
example: n = 10 = 2*5 = prime(1)*prime(3) encodes strict partition [1,4] having seven lambda-parking functions: [1,1], [1,2], [2,1], [1,3], [3,1], [1,4], [4,1], thus a(10) = 7.
results.author: _Alois P. Heinz_, Dec 02 2015
